  "description": "The founding prophet of Zoroastrianism, who received <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Divine\" data-tradition=\"persian\" href=\"../../../mythos/persian/index.html\" title=\"View divine in ancient texts\">divine</a> revelation from <a class=\"inline-search-link\" href=\"../deities/ahura-mazda.html\">Ahura Mazda</a> and established the <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Religion\" data-tradition=\"persian\" href=\"../../../mythos/persian/index.html\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Religion'\">religion</a> of <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Truth\" data-tradition=\"persian\" href=\"../../../mythos/persian/index.html\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Truth'\">truth</a>. <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Zoroaster\" data-tradition=\"persian\" href=\"../../../mythos/persian/index.html\" title=\"View zoroaster in ancient texts\">Zoroaster</a> (Avestan: <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Zarathustra\" data-tradition=\"persian\" href=\"../../../mythos/persian/index.html\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Zarathustra'\">Zarathustra</a>; Persian: <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Zartosht\" data-tradition=\"persian\" href=\"../../../mythos/persian/index.html\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Zartosht'\">Zartosht</a>) is revered as humanity's greatest teacher, the one who revealed the cosmic conflict between <a class=\"inline-search-link\" href=\"../cosmology/asha.html\">Asha</a> and <a class=\"inline-search-link\" href=\"../cosmology/druj.html\">Druj</a>, and taught the <a class=\"inline-search-link\" href=\"../cosmology/threefold-path.html\">Threefold Path</a> of <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Righteousness\" data-tradition=\"persian\" href=\"../../../mythos/persian/index.html\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Righteousness'\">righteousness</a>.",
